               <p>WILLIAM LACEY. I am a <rs id="t18331017-48-viclabel272" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331017-48-victim551 t18331017-48-viclabel272"></join>. On the 29th of September, I was in <placeName id="t18331017-48-crimeloc273">Norton-Falgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18331017-48-crimeloc273" type="placeName" value="Norton-Falgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18331017-48-crimeloc273" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331017-48-off270 t18331017-48-crimeloc273"></join>, about half-past ten o'clock in the evening - I felt my handkerchief taken from my pocket - I turned and saw the prisoner run - I pursued him; he threw my handkerchief down - I did not lose sight of him till he was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331017-48-person552">
                  THOMAS 
                  GOODING
